      "Replaced handle on wheel unit fire extinguisher",
      "Replaced punctured hydraulic hose"
    ],
    "summary": "On 17 March 2025 at 2140 hours, during well abandonment operations at Eugene Island Block 307A, a single joint of 3.5-inch pipe fell approximately 40 feet to the deck. The incident occurred when a crane operator, without clear line of sight, lowered the pipe onto a Self-Retracting Lifeline (SRL) Arm in an elevated hydraulic jack basket. When the floor hand pushed the pipe off the SRL arm, the impact caused worn elevator doors to open, releasing the pipe. Two workers in the area moved out of the way before the pipe struck a hydraulic hose and fire extinguisher handle. No injuries or pollution occurred; damages totaled $4,000.",
